    • Uses of IndexedSeq in javaslang

      Methods in javaslang that return types with arguments of type IndexedSeq 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      default Iterator<IndexedSeq<T>> Iterable.grouped(int size)
      Groups this Traversable into fixed size blocks like so: If this.isEmpty(), the resulting Traversable is empty. If size <= this.length(), the resulting Traversable will contain this.length() / size blocks of size size and maybe a non-empty block of size this.length() % size, if there are remaining elements. If size > this.length(), the resulting Traversable will contain one block of size this.length(). Examples:
      default Iterator<IndexedSeq<T>> Iterable.sliding(int size)
      Slides a window of a specific size and step size 1 over this TraversableOnce by calling Iterable.sliding(int, int).
      default Iterator<IndexedSeq<T>> Iterable.sliding(int size, int step)
      Slides a window of a specific size and step size over this TraversableOnce.
